From: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Date: Mon, 18 Apr 2022 06:53:11 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] loop: remove a spurious clear of discard_alignment
Git-commit: 4418bfd8fb9602d9cd8747c3ad52fdbaa02e2ffd
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
References: jsc#PED-1183

The loop driver never sets a discard_alignment, so it also doens't need
to clear it to zero.

Signed-off-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Reviewed-by: Damien Le Moal <damien.lemoal@opensource.wdc.com>
Reviewed-by: Chaitanya Kulkarni <kch@nvidia.com>
Reviewed-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20220418045314.360785-9-hch@lst.de
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.com>
---
 drivers/block/loop.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/block/loop.c b/drivers/block/loop.c
index 0c7f0367200c..322d92f958ea 100644
--- a/drivers/block/loop.c
+++ b/drivers/block/loop.c
@@ -798,7 +798,6 @@ static void loop_config_discard(struct loop_device *lo)
 		blk_queue_max_discard_sectors(q, 0);
 		blk_queue_max_write_zeroes_sectors(q, 0);
 	}
-	q->limits.discard_alignment = 0;
 }
 
 struct loop_worker {
